originalText.text: Filling fell off twice within 6 months. He suggested to do crown. It was a simple and small cavity to begin with but after refilling and drilled deeper. It can get worse and end up loss the whole teeth. It’s about money. I switched to other dentist and do the filling without crown. The filling stayed for a year already. Another experience is that he refused to prescribe pain killer and antibiotics after taking the tooth off. Other dentist gives it when you ask.  Zero star it deserves.

originalText.text: I came here for an EMERGENCY tooth extraction!!!! They charged my insurance and did ABSOLUTELY nothing but make me wait in a chair for THREE hours! I do NOT recommend I will NOT be back! I am definitely NOT using their referral!!! Clearly all they care about is CHARGING your insurance. I should’ve taken heed on the reviews!! This place is a complete joke and SCAM!

originalText.text: My mother saw this dentist twice, and it was a bad experience both times. She got a crown for one of her tooth the first time, and it caused her pain for months and dentist told her it was normal. She went back recently to have him fix a small filling on her front tooth, and within a few days the filling came off! DO NOT RECOMMEND THIS DENTIST AT ALL!

Clean facility. Doctor not understanding at all. I missed 3 appointments due to other health conditions and they "terminated" me. I had several intense and necessary procedures scheduled, dentist doesn't care.

If you have a busy schedule or unpredictable kids or any kind of medical ailment DO NOT choose this dentist.
